modules.description: Provides functions to serialize and deserialize Unix.file_descrs for transmission over Unix domain sockets. Operates on file descriptors and byte sequences, enabling inter-process communication. Used to pass open files between processes in a Unix environment.

Provides functions to transmit and receive file descriptors over UNIX domain sockets, using byte buffers or strings for data. Operates on Unix file descriptors, byte arrays, and string values, enabling low-level inter-process communication. Sends and receives file descriptors alongside message data, useful for passing open files between processes.
